^r)$, with $k=q^r+q$. The above\nresults do not hold true for $r=2$ and there remain open the case $r=3$ for the\nHermitian curve, and the cases $r=3,4$ for the rational BKS curve. As a by\nproduct we also obtain two results of interest in the study of the Galois\ninverse problem for $\\mathrm{PGL}(2,q)$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Feb 2023 18:49:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-21"}
